:::summary
The Pearl of Great Price is one of the four standard works (volumes of scripture) of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints. It is a compact but remarkably rich collection including the Book of Moses, the Book of Abraham, Joseph Smith — Matthew, Joseph Smith — History, and the Articles of Faith. These writings restore ancient truths, clarify doctrines from the Bible, and give a uniquely LDS window into pre-mortal existence, the creation, and the Abrahamic covenant.
:::

